title: Textile, 1851–63
medium:
Medium: cotton
Technique: printed by engraved roller and block printed
description: Ground molette printed in grey zig-zags which form moire pattern. Overprinted with sprays of roses and wild flowers in shades of dark red and white, form being given to the white roses by means of tiny dots. Trailing white ribbons, outlined by dots, connect the design elements.
